WEBVTT

01:19.121 --> 01:22.989
J oldies 99.2 &

01:23.083 --> 01:25.574
j kiou j

01:26.962 --> 01:28.982
well, the weekend forecast
looking good for the area.

01:29.006 --> 01:31.918
Sunny skies on tap from brentwood
all the way north to Richmond

01:32.009 --> 01:35.217
and throughout the state of Virginia,
with highs reaching 85 degrees.

01:35.304 --> 01:37.135
Low tonight, about 65.

01:37.222 --> 01:39.804
Should be a great weekend
for hikers to get out and enjoy...

01:55.282 --> 01:56.818
Pretty girl.

01:56.908 --> 01:58.444
You must be one proud papa.

02:02.664 --> 02:04.325
Who's the black fella?

02:05.667 --> 02:07.703
Darius clemmons. It's her boyfriend.

02:07.794 --> 02:10.786
They were traveling
with a group of their friends.

02:12.674 --> 02:14.986
Well, the appalachian trail's
a hefty piece of real estate.

02:15.010 --> 02:17.217
I mean, Maine clear down to Georgia way.

02:17.304 --> 02:19.886
I've been tracking their route,

02:19.973 --> 02:23.340
and she promised to call
or text every week.

02:23.435 --> 02:25.096
And it's been six weeks.

02:25.187 --> 02:29.556
The last place that she
texted me was here in your town.

02:31.610 --> 02:34.397
Well, the fact is we get a shit-ton
of kids that come through here.

02:34.488 --> 02:39.073
I mean, they come, and they do
whatever it is they do, and they move on.

02:39.910 --> 02:42.822
My boy's down in tampa
playing keyboard in some rockabilly band.

02:42.913 --> 02:44.974
I can't remember the last time
that boy picked up a phone.

02:44.998 --> 02:46.408
My daughter's not like that.

02:49.169 --> 02:52.286
Well, we can make it official
if you'd like.

02:53.090 --> 02:54.955
Fill out this missing persons report.

02:55.050 --> 02:57.086
Be as detailed as you'd like.

02:57.636 --> 02:59.592
But if I were to put money on it,

02:59.680 --> 03:02.797
I'd say she's somewhere
sunning herself in the keys.

03:04.976 --> 03:07.843
Guest checkout is automatic.
I rarely see them leave.

03:07.938 --> 03:12.398
Most are gone by sun up,
trying to catch flights or beat traffic.

03:12.484 --> 03:14.128
And there was nothing
left in the room?

03:14.152 --> 03:16.234
No. And their car was gone.

03:16.321 --> 03:17.561
Okay, well,

03:17.656 --> 03:21.569
if you think of anything,
please give me a call, yeah?

03:22.244 --> 03:23.244
My name's Scott.

03:26.039 --> 03:27.745
You spoke to the police chief?

03:27.833 --> 03:28.993
Yeah.

03:29.084 --> 03:30.949
I didn't sense much urgency from him.

03:31.044 --> 03:33.160
This is a quiet town.

03:33.755 --> 03:36.246
The quieter it is,
the more he gets to fish.

03:41.596 --> 03:43.052
Hey, it's Jen.

03:43.140 --> 03:46.052
Leave a message, and I'll hit you back.
Thanks, bye.

03:47.018 --> 03:49.259
Look again. Please.

03:49.354 --> 03:50.434
No, sorry, no.

03:50.522 --> 03:52.979
You know how many tourists
come through here?

03:53.066 --> 03:55.182
I remember drinks, not faces.

03:56.862 --> 03:58.318
Lose something?

04:01.867 --> 04:03.448
My daughter.

04:04.244 --> 04:06.200
Her name is Jennifer.

04:06.288 --> 04:09.655
She passed through here
with five of her friends.

04:10.208 --> 04:12.199
They're all about the same age.

04:12.294 --> 04:14.000
Yeah, I seen 'em.

04:14.921 --> 04:16.661
Goddamn yuppies.

04:17.716 --> 04:19.798
You didn't happen to notice
which way they went?

04:19.885 --> 04:20.885
North, maybe.

04:20.969 --> 04:22.755
Up on the at.

04:23.597 --> 04:28.591
But if they got lost in them woods,
you might as well just go on home,

04:28.977 --> 04:31.093
'cause you ain't never gonna find 'em.

04:32.564 --> 04:34.395
Yeah, well...

04:35.275 --> 04:38.062
I don't believe that. I can't.

04:38.153 --> 04:41.065
Believe what you want, mister.
But know this...

04:42.115 --> 04:44.197
Out there,

04:44.284 --> 04:49.654
nature eats everything it catches
right down to the bone.

04:49.748 --> 04:51.830
Doesn't give a shit if it's a cute girl.

04:59.424 --> 05:00.834
Do you have kids?

05:02.969 --> 05:04.755
What would you do?

05:49.599 --> 05:51.079
What do you think of this one?

05:51.685 --> 05:53.221
Yeah, it's-it's fine.

05:53.311 --> 05:55.302
- Adam, come on.
- What? What the fuck?

05:55.397 --> 05:57.375
- I need that.
- I want to show you the picture.

05:57.399 --> 05:58.959
- Give me my phone.
- No!

05:58.984 --> 06:00.645
Hey. Babe, you're fine.

06:00.735 --> 06:03.101
Just breathe.

06:03.196 --> 06:04.902
Open your mind.

06:04.990 --> 06:06.196
Enjoy it, okay?

06:06.283 --> 06:09.116
- Look at that one.
- Is that how sad I look all the time?

06:09.202 --> 06:10.908
Yes, you do, actually.

06:10.996 --> 06:13.032
I must really love you.

06:13.123 --> 06:16.081
You really do.
It's-it's weird how much you love...

06:16.167 --> 06:17.498
You're weird.

06:18.128 --> 06:19.618
Now kiss me.

06:22.716 --> 06:24.172
- Whoa!
- Ah!

06:29.431 --> 06:32.969
You know, uh,
you're making me look bad.

06:33.059 --> 06:35.926
- Sorry.
- Don't be. Fucking girl power.

06:36.021 --> 06:38.558
Girl power.

06:38.648 --> 06:41.936
Dude, where'd you
learn how to do this?

06:42.027 --> 06:43.892
My dad.

06:43.987 --> 06:45.147
He taught me two things:

06:45.238 --> 06:48.321
How to bait a hook
and how to change a tire.

06:48.408 --> 06:50.364
My dad taught me how to put in a tampon.

06:52.162 --> 06:53.277
Single parent.

06:53.371 --> 06:54.861
His eyes were closed the whole time.

06:54.956 --> 06:56.162
Not a good experience.

06:56.249 --> 06:57.864
Uh...

07:01.296 --> 07:03.287
Oh.

07:03.381 --> 07:04.621
- Oh, here we go.
- Sweet.

07:04.674 --> 07:06.130
Jen, Jen, Jen.

07:06.217 --> 07:07.798
My fucking hero.

07:12.474 --> 07:13.554
It's quaint.

07:13.642 --> 07:18.727
Yeah, especially if you miss
the good old days of the confederacy.

07:26.780 --> 07:28.190
All right.

07:28.281 --> 07:29.817
This one's mine.

07:29.908 --> 07:31.719
- That's yours, babe.
- Trying to grab yours.

07:31.743 --> 07:32.949
Pass me mine.

07:41.836 --> 07:43.997
- Three rooms for two nights.
- Yes.

07:44.089 --> 07:46.922
Policies of the inn
are posted in your rooms.

07:47.008 --> 07:48.748
No alcohol on the patio.

07:48.843 --> 07:52.006
No candles in the room,
no loud music or raucous activity.

07:52.097 --> 07:54.258
Hear that, boys? Behave yourselves.

07:57.894 --> 08:01.386
Thanks. And don't worry.
I'll keep them on a short leash.

08:01.481 --> 08:03.017
Have you been here before?

08:04.067 --> 08:06.524
First time.
Just doing a little hiking.

08:06.611 --> 08:11.275
Piece of advice,
keep to the marked trail.

08:11.366 --> 08:15.154
The land here can be unforgiving.

08:17.706 --> 08:20.413
Thanks. We'll be careful.

08:41.479 --> 08:43.970
You know that a bunch of abolitionists
came from this town?

08:44.065 --> 08:47.978
Darius loves that shit.
Fucking history, baby.

08:48.069 --> 08:50.606
Back when people actually fought
for what they believed in.

08:50.697 --> 08:53.467
Listen, by the way, what was that...
What was that thing earlier?

08:53.491 --> 08:55.231
Why wouldn't you hold my hand?

08:55.326 --> 08:56.941
Nothing. No reason.

08:57.037 --> 08:58.277
Oh, there's a reason.

08:59.831 --> 09:01.412
Same reason Darius is on edge.

09:01.499 --> 09:02.784
- Adam.
- Dude.

09:02.876 --> 09:05.788
What? He's a black dude
with a white girlfriend

09:05.879 --> 09:07.244
in bum-fuck Virginia.

09:08.798 --> 09:10.208
Hey.

09:16.389 --> 09:18.880
Y'all ain't from around here, are you?

09:18.975 --> 09:20.886
What gave us away?

09:20.977 --> 09:22.183
Uh, yeah.

09:22.270 --> 09:26.058
We're just, uh, checking out
the appalachian trail.

09:26.149 --> 09:28.856
Couple days of hiking.
Nothing extreme.

09:28.943 --> 09:30.808
There's something dangerous up there.

09:30.904 --> 09:34.362
So if you got any questions
or you need a guide,

09:34.449 --> 09:36.906
me and my pals over here,
we, uh, we know this land

09:36.993 --> 09:39.405
like the back of our hands.

09:39.496 --> 09:42.033
Thanks. Thanks. I think we're good.

09:42.791 --> 09:44.201
It's your life.

09:44.292 --> 09:47.250
But, uh, if you change your mind...

09:48.213 --> 09:49.999
We'll always be around.

09:54.052 --> 09:57.215
Driving around in a shitty pickup,
sipping moonshine, am I right?

09:57.305 --> 09:58.511
Stop it.

09:58.598 --> 09:59.804
What'd you say, peckerwood?

09:59.891 --> 10:02.007
Excuse my fiancé.

10:02.102 --> 10:05.640
He forgets that talking to people
isn't like commenting on reddit.

10:06.940 --> 10:08.805
Don't look at me, boy.

10:10.735 --> 10:14.774
You goddamn hipster freaks
are the problem with this whole world.

10:14.864 --> 10:17.230
I'm betting not a goddamn one of you

10:17.325 --> 10:20.317
ever worked a real fucking job
in your life.

10:21.037 --> 10:24.120
So you better sit the fuck still
and behave yourself.

10:28.128 --> 10:29.789
You're wrong.

10:30.296 --> 10:31.376
Jen.

10:32.090 --> 10:35.048
My boyfriend, Darius,
runs a sustainable energy nonprofit.

10:35.135 --> 10:37.672
Milla's an oncologist.
Adam's an app developer.

10:37.762 --> 10:40.253
And Gary and Luis own a pair
of New York bistros.

10:40.348 --> 10:43.135
I don't know. I'd call those real jobs.

10:44.018 --> 10:46.304
And what about you, sweetheart?

10:46.396 --> 10:47.602
I have two master's.

10:47.689 --> 10:49.395
Art history and dance.

10:49.482 --> 10:51.347
Which means I make coffee for a living.

10:52.861 --> 10:54.351
But right now I'm looking at you,

10:54.445 --> 10:56.048
and I'm seeing some
yellowing in your eyes.

10:56.072 --> 10:58.233
Which means what, Milla? Hmm?

10:58.324 --> 11:01.407
Oh, um, it could be liver problems.

11:01.494 --> 11:04.611
Jaundice, hepatitis, Gilbert syndrome.

11:04.706 --> 11:07.322
You should probably
see a doctor, actually.

11:11.671 --> 11:13.377
All right, well...

11:13.464 --> 11:15.796
You kids be safe.

11:17.385 --> 11:19.501
Maybe we'll see you again.

11:24.559 --> 11:27.301
Seriously, do not do that ever again.

11:27.395 --> 11:29.415
- I can't handle that.
- Dude, why do we let you drink?

11:29.439 --> 11:30.679
Because usually I'm very funny.

11:30.773 --> 11:33.185
No, actually, you have never,
ever been funny.

11:33.276 --> 11:34.482
Like, never.

11:34.569 --> 11:35.934
Where are the drinks?

11:39.365 --> 11:40.730
You know this song.

11:40.825 --> 11:42.611
Do you know this?

11:42.702 --> 11:44.658
No, but it's a good song.

11:59.052 --> 12:01.885
Okay, people, 8:00 A.M.

12:01.971 --> 12:04.007
Luis, Gary, I'm talking to you.

12:04.098 --> 12:05.759
Okay, I'm not a morning person.

12:05.850 --> 12:07.841
If I don't get my eight hours,
I will be a zombie.

12:07.936 --> 12:09.830
- Be a zombie who hikes.
- Hey, guys.

12:09.854 --> 12:12.015
- Guys.
- What?

12:12.106 --> 12:14.597
Who's that by the car?

12:14.692 --> 12:16.808
Is that one of those assholes
from the bar?

12:16.903 --> 12:18.768
Yeah, probably.

12:18.863 --> 12:20.819
- Hey.
- Adam.

12:20.907 --> 12:22.863
- Relax.
- Hey!

12:22.951 --> 12:24.942
Get away from the car, man.

12:25.954 --> 12:28.115
Get away from there. Shoo.

12:28.206 --> 12:30.117
- He's not a dog.
- Yo!

12:30.208 --> 12:33.450
Are you deaf or something?
Back the fuck off!

12:34.462 --> 12:38.171
Jesus, Adam, are you trying
to piss off everyone in middle America?

12:38.258 --> 12:39.919
You gotta be tough with these people.

12:40.009 --> 12:41.419
Okay, big guy, time for bed.

12:41.511 --> 12:42.751
- Come on.
- Back me up here.

12:42.845 --> 12:44.460
Adam.

12:44.555 --> 12:46.045
Come on, forget about it.

12:46.140 --> 12:47.755
Where the hell did that guy go?

12:47.850 --> 12:49.511
Come on.

12:49.602 --> 12:51.217
Hi this is Scott.

12:51.312 --> 12:53.290
Leave a message and I'll get
right back to you. Thank you.

12:53.314 --> 12:56.181
Hey, dad. Sorry to call so late.

12:56.276 --> 12:58.187
We're still hiking the appalachian trail.

12:58.278 --> 13:00.238
When I get back,
I promise I'll give you an answer

13:00.280 --> 13:01.861
about what I plan to do.

13:04.325 --> 13:06.190
I love you.

13:06.286 --> 13:07.571
Say hi to Corinne.

13:07.662 --> 13:09.493
Maybe she'll say hi back for a change.

13:10.707 --> 13:12.368
Okay, talk soon.

13:13.584 --> 13:15.165
Bye.

13:15.253 --> 13:18.165
So is Adam right?

13:18.256 --> 13:19.712
Are you on edge?

13:20.800 --> 13:22.040
We can go home right now.

13:22.135 --> 13:25.719
Hey, nice try,
but you don't have to protect me.

13:31.477 --> 13:35.095
You know why I work in nonprofit
instead of on wall street?

13:38.568 --> 13:39.808
Because...

13:42.071 --> 13:44.904
I want to build a community
where people are valued

13:44.991 --> 13:48.734
on their skills and their character.

13:50.913 --> 13:55.873
Not their bank account
or their skin color.

13:57.670 --> 13:59.035
Everyone works.

14:00.423 --> 14:02.288
Everyone shares.

14:05.136 --> 14:07.092
I'd give anything for that.

14:07.805 --> 14:09.591
I know.

14:12.060 --> 14:14.016
That's why I love you.

15:00.650 --> 15:03.687
These are beautiful.
Did you make all this?

15:04.654 --> 15:06.019
Some.

15:08.199 --> 15:09.484
Hey.

15:09.575 --> 15:12.157
I'm Jen. What's your name?

15:14.205 --> 15:16.867
Don't mind ruthie.

15:16.958 --> 15:18.289
She don't like to talk.

15:18.376 --> 15:20.207
I was shy too at her age.

15:20.294 --> 15:23.127
- Is she yours?
- In a manner.

15:23.214 --> 15:26.126
It takes a village to raise a child,
isn't that what they say?

15:26.926 --> 15:27.961
How much?

15:28.052 --> 15:29.337
Ten dollars.

15:37.437 --> 15:38.973
Thanks.

15:41.774 --> 15:43.105
Good morning.

15:43.192 --> 15:45.023
I've literally never seen you wear this.

15:45.111 --> 15:46.976
- Wow. Wow.
- Okay.

15:48.531 --> 15:50.317
Yeah!

15:51.659 --> 15:53.820
Walk of shame.

16:02.211 --> 16:05.044
Hey, what's up, you guys?
Me and Gary are going on a hike.

16:05.131 --> 16:06.917
I didn't know that you were filming.

16:07.008 --> 16:09.340
Everyone's here.
Yeah, it's for a YouTube video.

16:23.316 --> 16:24.316
Catch me.

16:26.986 --> 16:29.068
Oh, my god! Help!

16:30.656 --> 16:34.023
Oh, it's beautiful. Nature.

16:34.118 --> 16:36.109
Is anyone still drunk from last night?

16:36.204 --> 16:38.115
Bitch, I am.

16:38.206 --> 16:39.696
That last shot was a bad idea.

16:40.166 --> 16:42.327
Wait, looks like the trail ends.

16:42.418 --> 16:45.160
Are we going this way,
or are we going this way?

16:45.254 --> 16:47.119
Do you have signal on your phone?

16:47.632 --> 16:48.712
No.

16:50.676 --> 16:52.883
- I can do that.
- I've been horrible.

16:52.970 --> 16:56.303
- Look at that.
- This is fucking awesome!

16:58.059 --> 16:59.799
Whoo!

17:07.401 --> 17:09.016
It's up here.

17:13.782 --> 17:15.147
Okay?

17:47.692 --> 17:49.212
Do you know where we're going?

17:49.277 --> 17:50.141
I don't.

17:50.236 --> 17:51.817
Do you know where we're going?

17:55.700 --> 17:58.533
Okay, quick little side trip, guys.

17:58.619 --> 18:00.155
- What?
- There's supposed to be

18:00.246 --> 18:02.737
a very well-preserved
civil war fort near here.

18:02.832 --> 18:04.948
Cool. Let's find it.

18:05.042 --> 18:07.579
Um, the woman at the inn
said we shouldn't leave the trail.

18:07.670 --> 18:09.535
It's just a quick look around.

18:09.630 --> 18:13.043
Babe, if we don't find anything,
we'll just cut back over to the trail.

18:13.134 --> 18:16.626
You know what we wouldn't have found
if we would have stayed on the trail?

18:16.721 --> 18:18.928
Hmm? The waterfall.

18:19.015 --> 18:21.472
And that cliff, hmm?

18:21.559 --> 18:24.050
Come on. We'll be good.

18:27.189 --> 18:28.349
- Okay.
- Okay?

18:28.441 --> 18:31.023
She said yes!

18:31.110 --> 18:33.351
- Whoo! Whoo!
- Let's do it.

18:33.446 --> 18:34.798
What does that mean?
They getting married?

18:34.822 --> 18:36.382
Wait, just for the hike, right?

18:42.622 --> 18:44.032
You good?

18:45.750 --> 18:47.411
Such a hiker.

18:52.548 --> 18:54.334
What was that?

18:54.425 --> 18:56.131
- A snake.
- Oh, my god.

19:02.224 --> 19:03.589
- You okay?
- Yeah.

19:05.227 --> 19:06.558
We're good.

19:06.937 --> 19:08.893
- Shit. Yeah, thanks.
- Fuck.

19:19.867 --> 19:21.573
Ah!

19:26.415 --> 19:27.530
- You okay?
- Uh-huh.

19:28.167 --> 19:30.533
Dar, how much longer
is this gonna take?

19:30.628 --> 19:33.495
Look, it's just a little further, okay?
I promise, okay?

19:33.589 --> 19:34.669
Please.

19:34.757 --> 19:36.293
- You okay?
- No!

19:39.136 --> 19:41.252
We got to go.
We got to keep going.

19:42.056 --> 19:43.742
We've been walking
for fucking hours.

19:43.766 --> 19:44.630
That's what we've been doing.

19:44.725 --> 19:46.536
We've been walking
way more than an hour.

19:46.560 --> 19:48.680
What are you talking about?
It's been like four hours.

19:48.729 --> 19:50.290
- Four hours?
- No, I mean...

19:50.314 --> 19:52.020
I mean, since we passed that thing.

19:52.108 --> 19:53.644
You know what?

19:53.734 --> 19:57.522
Why don't you guys
just, um, just head back to the trail.

19:57.613 --> 19:58.978
I'll meet you guys up there.

20:01.325 --> 20:03.236
What is that?

20:09.250 --> 20:12.037
Oh, my god! Adam!

20:12.128 --> 20:13.743
- Oh, my god!
- Go, go, go, go, go.

20:17.425 --> 20:19.290
You guys, move left!

20:54.837 --> 20:56.373
Adam?

20:58.007 --> 21:00.043
Milla. Hey.

21:03.929 --> 21:05.294
You left me.

21:06.474 --> 21:09.307
- What?
- You left me.

21:09.393 --> 21:11.054
I know. I know. I'm sorry, okay?

21:11.145 --> 21:13.145
I was freaking out.
I didn't know what I was doing.

21:13.189 --> 21:14.770
- You left Mel
- I know. I'm sorry.

21:14.857 --> 21:16.893
You left me!

21:16.984 --> 21:18.724
Please, don't do that again!

21:18.819 --> 21:20.730
I'm so sorry, okay?

21:20.821 --> 21:22.482
Come here.

21:23.574 --> 21:24.734
Oh, fuck.

21:24.825 --> 21:26.440
Jen? Jen?

21:28.037 --> 21:30.028
Jen! Jen!

21:30.998 --> 21:31.998
Are you okay?

21:34.960 --> 21:36.245
- Are you okay?
- Yeah.

21:36.337 --> 21:37.873
Oh, my god, Darius! Your finger!

21:37.963 --> 21:39.373
Oh, fuck!

21:40.716 --> 21:43.082
We're okay. Oh, fuck.

21:43.886 --> 21:45.592
Where's Luis and Gary?

21:45.679 --> 21:47.010
Huh?

21:58.025 --> 22:00.107
Oh, shit.

22:05.491 --> 22:07.823
Luis. Luis, man. Get out of here.

22:07.910 --> 22:09.304
Come on. Let's go over here. Come on.

22:09.328 --> 22:10.613
No, no, no, no.

22:10.704 --> 22:12.535
- No, no! No!
- Let's go over here.

22:12.623 --> 22:14.739
Do not fucking touch me!

22:16.502 --> 22:18.208
Okay.

22:20.339 --> 22:21.829
