41:54.721 --> 41:58.885
You promised me you would never leave me.

42:09.777 --> 42:11.358
Help me.

42:12.739 --> 42:14.195
Help me.

42:18.953 --> 42:20.489
Help me.

42:57.742 --> 42:59.152
Come on, let's go.

43:58.219 --> 43:59.504
What the fuck was that?

43:59.595 --> 44:01.051
- Ah!
- Darius!

44:01.139 --> 44:03.346
Darius! Darius!

44:03.432 --> 44:05.514
Darius?

44:27.456 --> 44:28.536
Good morning.

44:28.624 --> 44:30.740
You're late. And you're carpool today.

44:30.835 --> 44:31.835
- I know.
- I have class.

44:31.919 --> 44:33.750
I got a meeting in saddle river
with a roofer

44:33.838 --> 44:35.065
and a concrete guy in millburn.

44:35.089 --> 44:36.625
- Hey.
- Hey.

44:36.716 --> 44:38.777
- You haven't heard from Jen, have you?
- Why would she call me?

44:38.801 --> 44:40.587
- Because you're her mom.
- Don't say "mom."

44:40.678 --> 44:44.546
She hates that. Get your stuff.
You have one minute.

44:44.640 --> 44:46.176
Jenny, it's your dad.

44:46.267 --> 44:50.180
I'm, uh, just calling again
to see how you're doing.

44:50.271 --> 44:53.058
I hope you're having fun
with your friends.

44:53.316 --> 44:55.898
Listen, I'd love to talk to you
about that offer.

44:55.985 --> 44:57.713
You'd get your own office
and your own coffee maker

44:57.737 --> 44:58.943
with all the perks.

44:59.030 --> 45:00.816
Excuse the pun.

45:00.907 --> 45:02.488
Anyhow...

45:03.743 --> 45:05.574
Don't forget to call me, all right?

45:05.661 --> 45:07.993
It's been a couple weeks now, and...

45:08.080 --> 45:10.366
I'd love to hear your voice.

45:10.458 --> 45:12.164
Please, give me a call.

45:12.251 --> 45:15.539
Thank you. I love you. Bye.

45:18.591 --> 45:19.751
Weird.

45:19.842 --> 45:21.048
It went to voicemail again.

45:22.511 --> 45:24.502
Want to know why she doesn't call?

45:24.597 --> 45:26.212
Jennifer went off to find herself,

45:26.307 --> 45:29.049
which is a choice she made
to avoid making a choice.

45:29.143 --> 45:33.603
Look, how about you focus
on my boys, our boys?

45:33.689 --> 45:35.225
For once.

45:35.316 --> 45:36.977
- Yeah.
- Please?

46:28.494 --> 46:29.859
Help!

46:31.497 --> 46:33.988
Help! Somebody, please!

46:34.542 --> 46:36.157
Help me!

46:39.005 --> 46:41.291
Stop your screaming,
or you'll suffer for it.

46:41.382 --> 46:43.088
You. I know you.

46:43.175 --> 46:45.006
Help me. Please help me.

46:45.094 --> 46:46.880
Do you want food? Water?

46:46.971 --> 46:48.586
- Yes.
- Then shut your mouth.

46:48.681 --> 46:49.966
Understand?

46:50.057 --> 46:51.513
Please, please, please, let me go.

46:51.600 --> 46:53.682
Please. You met me in town, remember?

46:53.769 --> 46:57.182
- You and the little girl? Ruthie?
- You don't want to listen.

46:57.273 --> 46:59.935
No. No, no, no, no, no, no, no!
I'm sorry!

47:00.026 --> 47:01.482
I'm sorry. Please.

47:01.569 --> 47:03.434
Please, please come back.

47:04.363 --> 47:05.899
Please!

47:11.329 --> 47:13.285
This isn't happening.

47:15.583 --> 47:17.244
This isn't happening!

48:07.093 --> 48:08.754
Milla?

48:19.355 --> 48:21.016
Walk.

49:31.177 --> 49:33.133
What the. .?

49:37.016 --> 49:38.381
Walk.

50:10.716 --> 50:12.252
Kneel.

50:13.511 --> 50:15.923
I'm done with this bullshit.

50:18.015 --> 50:19.380
Kneel.

50:19.934 --> 50:21.265
Fuck you.

50:26.065 --> 50:27.896
Jesus. They'll kill you, man.

50:29.151 --> 50:30.516
Stay down.

50:31.779 --> 50:33.269
Stay back.

51:23.080 --> 51:24.570
Oh, god.

51:24.665 --> 51:26.781
This is court.

51:26.875 --> 51:28.615
You are on trial.

51:29.795 --> 51:31.660
Trial? For what?

51:31.755 --> 51:33.336
Murder.

51:33.424 --> 51:36.211
This is bullshit!
We didn't murder anybody!

51:39.096 --> 51:40.586
Only you will speak.

51:42.224 --> 51:45.466
If you have questions,
my daughter will answer.

52:04.371 --> 52:07.829
You-you can't put us on trial.
This-this isn't a court of law.

52:07.916 --> 52:10.498
The law is the law.

52:10.586 --> 52:12.167
There's only truth and lies.

52:12.254 --> 52:16.748
This can't be happening.
This can't be happening.

52:16.842 --> 52:18.423
It's fucking insane!

52:20.804 --> 52:24.296
The next one who speaks
out of turn loses their tongue.

52:29.730 --> 52:31.186
Hobbs.

52:35.235 --> 52:39.945
I saw each of them,
in town and on the mountain.

52:43.285 --> 52:45.697
That one threw a bottle at me.

52:45.788 --> 52:48.029
- No, no.
- Jesus, Adam.

52:48.123 --> 52:51.581
He says vile words about us.

52:52.711 --> 52:54.497
He hates us.

53:07.351 --> 53:08.351
Morgan.

53:12.856 --> 53:15.222
Morgan...

53:15.317 --> 53:17.308
Tell us what you saw.

53:27.371 --> 53:28.861
Samuel...

53:32.459 --> 53:34.825
W-w-what is he saying?

53:36.964 --> 53:41.298
"My brother, Samuel,
and I were out hunting."

53:45.973 --> 53:49.932
"Stalking moose and elk
for the winter larder."

53:52.479 --> 53:58.520
"We were checking our game traps
in the cave where caught game is dragged

53:58.610 --> 54:00.726
to keep predators from getting to it."

54:02.573 --> 54:03.938
- Ah!
- Adam!

54:06.326 --> 54:10.911
"And we found
this stranger instead."

54:14.460 --> 54:19.454
"He was hurt, knocked out.
We were taking him down the mountain."

54:24.011 --> 54:26.593
"Planned to leave him
where he'd be found..."

54:34.313 --> 54:37.680
"When these others attacked us."

54:45.991 --> 54:49.575
"He killed my brother Samuel."

54:49.661 --> 54:51.652
No. We didn't know.

54:52.831 --> 54:54.367
They were wearing skulls,

54:54.458 --> 54:57.040
and their bodies were covered
with leaves and blood.

54:58.170 --> 55:01.253
What we wear when we go hunting, huh?

55:01.340 --> 55:05.049
To hide our scent and our faces
from our prey.

55:05.135 --> 55:06.841
Your hunters do the same.

55:06.929 --> 55:08.715
Hmm?

55:08.889 --> 55:12.052
Did he do what Morgan has accused?

55:12.142 --> 55:17.057
Did this man murder
Morgan's brother, Samuel?

55:18.649 --> 55:23.518
Lie, and dread will fall on each of you.

55:25.030 --> 55:26.645
I warn you.

55:27.366 --> 55:29.231
Speak true.

55:36.792 --> 55:37.952
No.

55:40.712 --> 55:42.623
He didn't murder him.

56:01.275 --> 56:02.606
Ruthie.

56:09.783 --> 56:13.275
Ruthie, who killed Samuel?

56:18.417 --> 56:20.499
You lied to this court.

56:21.670 --> 56:23.160
No, no.

56:23.255 --> 56:24.745
Adam feared for his life.

56:24.840 --> 56:27.172
He killed this man in self-defense.

56:27.259 --> 56:28.544
It's not murder.

56:28.635 --> 56:30.717
We thought they were kidnapping him.

56:30.804 --> 56:32.965
We thought they were taking him
somewhere to kill him.

56:33.056 --> 56:35.422
Why? Why did you think this?

56:35.517 --> 56:38.304
What proof did you have?

56:38.395 --> 56:41.182
Had you met any of our people?

56:41.940 --> 56:45.148
Had we caused you any harm?!

56:57.956 --> 57:01.448
This court finds you guilty of murder.

57:02.586 --> 57:04.793
- The sentence is death.
- What?

57:04.880 --> 57:07.496
No, no, no, I didn't...
It was a mistake.

57:07.591 --> 57:09.331
I didn't know what they were doing.

57:09.426 --> 57:11.587
It's not my fault!

57:14.806 --> 57:16.137
Gget back.

57:16.224 --> 57:18.135
You want this kid to join your brother?

57:18.226 --> 57:20.342
Then back the fuck off!

57:20.437 --> 57:21.847
Adam, Adam, no.

57:21.939 --> 57:24.476
- Shut up.
- Hey, hey, Adam.

57:24.566 --> 57:27.729
If you hurt her, you make things
worse for all of us.

57:27.819 --> 57:31.983
Look around, dar.
This shit's already worse.

57:32.074 --> 57:34.156
Okay, this is what you're gonna do.

57:34.242 --> 57:40.078
You're going to untie my friends,
and then you're going to let us go.

57:40.165 --> 57:43.032
I'm not afraid of you!

57:43.126 --> 57:46.243
I just want to get as far away
from you backwoods fucks

57:46.338 --> 57:47.544
as I possibly can.

57:48.507 --> 57:49.667
Now, move.

57:49.758 --> 57:51.840
I look in your eyes.

57:53.303 --> 57:55.339
I see only fear.

57:56.640 --> 57:58.676
There's no future for men like you.

58:00.394 --> 58:01.634
Fuck you!

58:04.481 --> 58:07.063
I was wrong to call you a man.

58:09.778 --> 58:13.441
The rest of you are guilty
for bearing false witness.

58:13.532 --> 58:15.113
The sentence is darkness.

58:15.200 --> 58:16.986
What? No, no, no. Please, please.

58:17.077 --> 58:19.443
- Take them.
- Please, please, no.

58:19.538 --> 58:21.369
Please, no! No!

58:24.376 --> 58:25.912
Jen! Jen!

58:29.381 --> 58:30.746
Jen!

58:56.908 --> 59:01.368
This family is owed retribution.

59:01.455 --> 59:03.741
How was Samuel murdered?

59:03.832 --> 59:07.040
Say the words.

59:07.127 --> 59:10.244
How was Samuel murdered?

59:18.930 --> 59:20.841
He was struck in the head.

59:32.444 --> 59:33.729
With this.

59:38.200 --> 59:39.485
No, no, no, no, no.

59:39.576 --> 59:40.691
No, don't do this.

59:40.786 --> 59:42.947
Don't do this, please.

59:43.038 --> 59:45.450
Please. It's wrong.

59:45.540 --> 59:47.246
It's barbaric.

59:47.334 --> 59:48.790
Listen to me, listen to me.

59:48.877 --> 59:50.788
We can help you.

59:51.671 --> 59:52.911
We'll do anything.

59:53.006 --> 59:55.122
- We can get you money...
- Barbaric?

59:55.217 --> 59:56.707
Hmm?

59:56.885 --> 01:00:00.093
Our families built this place.

01:00:00.180 --> 01:00:03.217
Men and women of all races and creeds

01:00:03.308 --> 01:00:08.928
came here to avoid the armageddon
they knew was coming between the states.

01:00:09.022 --> 01:00:11.934
We have everything we need.

01:00:12.025 --> 01:00:17.190
Everyone works.
Everyone contributes.

01:00:17.280 --> 01:00:20.067
Our food is fresh and plentiful.

01:00:20.158 --> 01:00:24.527
We have no cancer, no poverty, no war.

01:00:24.621 --> 01:00:29.240
No one hates another
because they have while another doesn't.

01:00:29.334 --> 01:00:33.543
We are one body working together.

01:00:39.845 --> 01:00:45.385
You tell me, whose world is more barbaric?

01:00:52.941 --> 01:00:54.772
Nol

01:01:06.288 --> 01:01:07.778
Take them.

01:01:22.304 --> 01:01:25.296
Your sentence is darkness.

01:01:25.390 --> 01:01:29.178
Here, you will see no evil,

01:01:29.269 --> 01:01:32.386
hear no evil, speak no evil.

01:01:35.775 --> 01:01:37.606
No!

01:01:43.491 --> 01:01:45.197
Oh, no!

01:01:45.285 --> 01:01:46.991
No, wait. Please, no.

01:01:47.078 --> 01:01:48.363
Jen!

01:01:48.455 --> 01:01:50.241
No! No!

01:01:55.295 --> 01:01:58.002
Ah! Don't!

01:01:58.089 --> 01:01:59.875
Darius! Darius, help me!

01:01:59.966 --> 01:02:01.922
I'm s 0 ry! I'm s 0 ry

01:02:02.010 --> 01:02:04.717
no! Help me! No! Please!

01:02:04.804 --> 01:02:05.990
Please, dear god. Please don't.

01:02:06.014 --> 01:02:08.005
No! No!

01:02:27.953 --> 01:02:29.068
Fuck off.

01:02:36.544 --> 01:02:37.704
Listen to me.

01:02:37.796 --> 01:02:39.752
You're making a mistake.

01:02:39.839 --> 01:02:42.171
You're wasting valuable resources...

01:02:44.094 --> 01:02:46.756
What are we wasting?

01:02:46.846 --> 01:02:48.256
Us.

01:02:48.348 --> 01:02:49.758
Us. Us.

01:02:49.849 --> 01:02:51.555
You-you have us.

01:02:51.643 --> 01:02:52.928
Use us.

01:02:53.019 --> 01:02:54.759
Darius works in nonprofit.

01:02:54.854 --> 01:02:57.687
- He works in sustainable energy.
- What the hell are you doing?

01:02:57.774 --> 01:03:01.483
He's designed homes, neighborhoods,
communities to be self-sufficient.

01:03:01.569 --> 01:03:03.025
We're already self-sufficient.

01:03:03.113 --> 01:03:06.071
No, but you need maintenance,
improvements.

01:03:06.157 --> 01:03:08.819
You suffer storm damage, climate changes.

01:03:08.910 --> 01:03:11.401
Springs dry up. You need problems solved.

01:03:11.496 --> 01:03:12.906
That's what he does.

01:03:14.582 --> 01:03:15.867
That's his skill.

01:03:15.959 --> 01:03:17.449
That's what he can contribute.

01:03:17.544 --> 01:03:20.786
You do this, you lose all of that.

01:03:20.880 --> 01:03:24.043
Standard says you're strong.

01:03:24.134 --> 01:03:25.749
You have a warrior spirit.

01:03:27.470 --> 01:03:28.960
I don't give up.

01:03:31.349 --> 01:03:32.805
And what of you?

01:03:32.892 --> 01:03:34.974
What do you offer?

01:03:41.901 --> 01:03:43.266
Myself.

01:03:47.991 --> 01:03:50.107
There's no sickness in my family.

01:03:51.536 --> 01:03:53.197
No cancer.

01:03:54.789 --> 01:03:58.407
I'm young, healthy.

01:04:00.045 --> 01:04:02.627
I'll have strong, healthy children.

01:04:11.931 --> 01:04:14.092
Who among your men needs a wife?

01:04:15.643 --> 01:04:17.053
No.

01:04:25.028 --> 01:04:26.438
Open your mouth.

01:04:32.619 --> 01:04:33.734
Shut up.

01:04:36.956 --> 01:04:38.571
Spread your legs.

01:04:41.002 --> 01:04:42.287
Spread your legs.

01:04:42.379 --> 01:04:44.085
Edith.

01:05:04.067 --> 01:05:08.231
Are you prepared to become
a loyal citizen?

01:05:09.989 --> 01:05:11.399
Yes.

01:05:16.579 --> 01:05:19.821
Are you prepared to become
a loyal citizen?

01:05:19.916 --> 01:05:21.622
Yes.

01:05:23.211 --> 01:05:29.298
If you run, you should know
there's no safe way off this mountain.

01:05:29.467 --> 01:05:33.631
If our traps don't kill you,
the animals will.

01:05:33.721 --> 01:05:38.010
If the land doesn't kill you,
our people will.

01:05:38.101 --> 01:05:43.016
If you don't contribute...
You'll end up here.

01:05:45.066 --> 01:05:46.556
Do you understand?

01:05:49.362 --> 01:05:51.227
Yes.

01:05:55.410 --> 01:05:57.071
Yeah. Yeah.

01:06:22.020 --> 01:06:23.635
Please don't hate me.

01:06:39.162 --> 01:06:40.777
Vee nor.

01:06:47.170 --> 01:06:48.876
Vee nor.

01:06:50.632 --> 01:06:52.088
Vee nor what...?

01:06:53.092 --> 01:06:54.252
"Friends?"

01:06:54.344 --> 01:06:55.834
Does that mean "friends?"

01:07:06.898 --> 01:07:08.638
Come with me.

01:07:57.198 --> 01:08:00.486
I've had no wife for a year.

01:08:07.375 --> 01:08:10.117
She died in a fall.

01:08:13.089 --> 01:08:17.173
Here, people die
of either accidents or old age.

01:08:21.471 --> 01:08:23.008
Can we ever leave?

01:08:28.604 --> 01:08:30.595
Why would you want to?

01:08:41.033 --> 01:08:43.524
I know about life below.

01:08:44.662 --> 01:08:46.198
You're alone.

01:08:49.042 --> 01:08:52.455
People come to the mountains
looking for something.

01:08:52.545 --> 01:08:57.960
Something to remind them
that life is worth living.

01:09:03.680 --> 01:09:05.763
You came looking for something.

01:09:11.104 --> 01:09:12.890
And now you've found it.

01:09:32.627 --> 01:09:35.663
You're not as strong as you pretend to be.

01:10:05.159 --> 01:10:06.945
Hey, it's Jen.

01:10:07.036 --> 01:10:08.742
Leave a message, and I'll hit you back.

01:10:08.830 --> 01:10:10.491
Thanks. Bye.

01:10:10.581 --> 01:10:12.446
The mailbox is full

01:10:12.542 --> 01:10:14.622
and cannot accept any messages
at this time. Goodbye.

01:10:17.296 --> 01:10:19.002
Hi.

01:10:19.090 --> 01:10:21.547
No. I don't know.

01:10:21.634 --> 01:10:23.215
Maybe a couple more days.

01:10:23.302 --> 01:10:26.635
I'm waiting to hear back
from the local police before I move on.

01:10:28.266 --> 01:10:29.802
I know.

01:10:29.892 --> 01:10:32.679
She's, uh... she's missing.

01:10:52.957 --> 01:10:54.413
Hello.

01:10:55.793 --> 01:10:57.829
I'm sorry about your daughter
and her friends.

01:10:57.920 --> 01:11:00.582
- Double whiskey.
- Thank you.

01:11:01.966 --> 01:11:04.503
I told her to stay on the trail.

01:11:05.928 --> 01:11:08.886
There are people living on that mountain.

01:11:10.975 --> 01:11:12.886
What people?

01:11:16.439 --> 01:11:17.849
The foundation.

01:11:19.150 --> 01:11:20.856
The foundation?

01:11:20.943 --> 01:11:24.356
It's a story people here know
but don't talk about,

01:11:24.447 --> 01:11:26.233
except in whispers.

01:11:26.324 --> 01:11:27.860
Like a ghost story.

01:11:27.950 --> 01:11:29.156
On.

01:11:29.243 --> 01:11:34.738
In 1859, a dozen or so families
packed up and fled up the mountain.

01:11:34.832 --> 01:11:39.201
They feared the collapse of America,
and wanted to protect their way of life.

01:11:39.670 --> 01:11:41.581
They said when America fell,

01:11:41.672 --> 01:11:47.167
they would be the foundation
on which a new nation would be built.

01:11:48.554 --> 01:11:52.342
And these descendants of these people

01:11:52.433 --> 01:11:56.017
are still living up there on the mountain?

01:11:56.103 --> 01:11:58.594
We don't bother them,
and they don't bother us.

01:11:58.689 --> 01:12:04.309
But anyone who goes up there,
they don't come back...

01:12:04.403 --> 01:12:06.689
Alive or dead.

01:12:08.741 --> 01:12:10.857
And you know this how?

01:12:10.952 --> 01:12:13.364
It's happened before.

01:12:13.454 --> 01:12:14.910
But if it's happened before,

01:12:14.997 --> 01:12:17.704
why hasn't someone
done something about it?

01:12:18.626 --> 01:12:20.082
Because...

01:12:20.545 --> 01:12:23.753
It's made to look like they left.

01:12:24.882 --> 01:12:26.668
I'm sorry.

01:12:55.913 --> 01:12:57.778
You just don't listen, do you, mister?

01:13:04.672 --> 01:13:08.506
Your girl is dead,
and you don't want to find what's left.

01:13:08.593 --> 01:13:10.504
She's not dead.

01:13:12.597 --> 01:13:14.508
Oh, you son of a...

01:13:19.520 --> 01:13:21.806
Hold on, hold on, hold on, hold on.

01:13:21.898 --> 01:13:24.014
Hey.

01:13:24.108 --> 01:13:25.598
Hey!

01:13:27.320 --> 01:13:28.526
No, no, no.

01:13:28.613 --> 01:13:30.023
No! No!

01:13:30.197 --> 01:13:31.903
- Get him up.
- Hey!

01:13:31.991 --> 01:13:34.903
You son of a bitch.

01:13:59.644 --> 01:14:01.680
Oh, shit.

01:14:06.317 --> 01:14:08.228
What are you doing?

01:14:08.319 --> 01:14:09.980
What does it look like I'm doing?

01:14:10.237 --> 01:14:11.602
You don't want to go up there.

01:14:11.697 --> 01:14:14.313
She's my daughter. I'm gonna find her.

01:14:14.408 --> 01:14:15.272
Scott...

01:14:15.368 --> 01:14:17.575
And there's nothing you can do to stop me.

01:14:17.662 --> 01:14:19.368
Jesus. What happened?

01:14:19.956 --> 01:14:23.540
Whatever happened to you
is nothing compared to what they'll do.

